FBIS4-41751 "drsov124_b_94017" FBIS-SOV-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Economics Minister Promises Tax Cuts `Soon' Economics Minister Promises Tax Cuts `Soon' LD2706173094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 LD2706173094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] Russian Economics Minister Aleksandr Shokhin claims the number of taxes will be cut down in Russia soon, the taxation system will become simpler while the tax burden will be reduced by 20 percent on the average. At the same time, according to him, financial discipline will be stepped up. The vice premier said the government plans to postpone temporarily the payment of VAT on imported equipment to speed up its import in Russia. He noted that the State Duma is prepared to back this decision, RIA reports.
